snippet.textDisplay:
Hey Matt, architect friend from Houston here, that guardrail is not to code. Will be difficult to pass building inspection and TAS inspection. Unless your AHJ (Authority Having Jurisdiction) allows for it the horizontal rungs on the stair are not permitted and will have to be vertical. Also couldn't tell from the video but they cannot allow more than a 4" sphere to pass through to meet code. Not that it has been installed but the handrail needs to be set clear inside of guardrail. 1.5" clear min with a rounded grip surface with max grip perimeter of 4 to 6 1/2". I would suggest adding a 1 1/2" wood (match finish of the treads) handrail. Also the stair risers have to be filled cannot be open ( you could have metal mesh welded on to close them but stay "open".



Love what ya'll do on all of your channels.
